claims-statement.p:
Claim 1 is amended to concretely specify the following features. In the preamble,

engagement permission means (M2) that permits engagement of the lockup clutch (LC) when a water temperature (Tw) of the engine detected by the temperature sensor (Sa, Sb) is less than a first set temperature (T1) but at least a second set temperature (T2) which is less than the first set temperature (T1);

In the characterized part,
the device comprises vehicle speed detecting means (Sc) detecting a vehicle speed (V);
when the water temperature (Tw) of the engine detected by the temperature sensor (Sa, Sb) is less than the second set temperature (T2), the vehicle speed (V) detected by the vehicle speed detecting means (Sc) is at least the predetermined value (VO), and the control region determination means (M3) determines that the running conditions of the vehicle are in the tight region, the engagement permission means (M2) permits engagement of the lockup clutch (LC).
